description: Moldova voted in favor of adding a path to the European Union to its constitution, and gave the incumbent president the most votes in elections Sunday, but neither result was the win leaders wanted.
title: Moldova barely approves its EU referendum amid allegations of Russian interference

description: Bomb threats are causing disruptions, diversions and delays for scores of flights on multiple Indian airlines. Indian authorities said they were looking to increase punishments for perpetrators.
title: Fake bomb threats disrupt travel for scores of flights on Indian airlines

description: Tribal communities often face obstacles to casting a ballot, including a lack of polling locations and unreliable mail service. In Nevada, Native voters can now cast a ballot online.
title: Nevada online tribal voting

description: Record-breaking TV ratings helped the WNBA secure a more lucrative media rights deal this year. Now, the players' union has opted out of its contract, a move aimed at better salaries and benefits.
title: As the WNBA's historic season comes to an end, players say it's time for higher pay

description:
The former Soviet republic of Moldova narrowly passed a referendum to pursue membership in the European Union. That puts it at odds with Russia, which is accused of meddling in the election. Our correspondent in Moscow tells us what the vote could mean.

And we go to the bar in Paris that for over a century has held a U.S. presidential straw poll that is usually accurate.
title: Russia Versus the West in Moldova's Election

description: A Michigan state judge has dismissed a Republican lawsuit that challenged the swing state’s long-standing process for voting by U.S. citizens living abroad, including military members.
title: A Michigan judge tosses out a Republican lawsuit over overseas and military voting

description: Michele Morrow has a track record of falsehoods - for example, saying Islam is a cult and that the plus in LGTBTQ+ stands for pedophilia.
title: GOP candidate for NC schools chief has spread conspiracy theories, ‘groomer’ rhetoric

description: What you need to know about the races, issues and decisions being made in your community.
title: Local voter guides: Find candidate information and resources in your community

description: Both liberal and conservative lawyers have judge-shopped, but in recent years, some conservative-leaning groups have been laser focused on bringing their challenges  in the Fifth Circuit Court of Appeals.
title: A frustrated Supreme Court to look at one version of judge shopping

description: Houston officials say the helicopter was flying from Ellington Airport when it crashed into a radio tower.
title: Multiple people dead after helicopter crash in Houston

description: Israel's military carried out airstrikes overnight on targets in Lebanon that the military says belong to Al-Qard Al-Hassan, a financial institution that undergirds the militant group Hezbollah.
title: Lebanon assesses the damage after Israel strikes Hezbollah-linked banks

description: “I kept on guessing and just taking risks,” says farmer Stephen Nzioka of Kenya. A weekly text message has been a game changer as he copes with a changing climate.
title: This farmer 'planted blindly' in a changing climate. A weather app came to his rescue

description: Why Pennsylvania is being closely watched this election. And, Israeli strikes on Lebanon hit branches of a Hezbollah-run financial institution.
title: What's important to Pennsylvania voters. And, Israel targets Hezbollah finances.

description: The reclusive U.S.-based Islamic cleric who inspired a global social movement while facing accusations he masterminded a failed 2016 coup in his native Turkey was in his eighties.
title: Self-exiled Turkish spiritual leader Fethullah Gülen dies in Pennsylvania

description: Sergeant Joshua Abate says that he's not a rioter or an insurrectionist. Those closest to the active-duty Marine call him "a good guy." But he was part of the mob that attacked the Capitol on January 6th, 2021. On the eve of a new presidential election, what does his case tell us, as the nation still grapples with the legacy of that day? As they look into the military's reckoning with extremism in the ranks, NPR's Tom Bowman and Lauren Hodges examine Abate's main line of defense: Don't focus on what he did; focus on his promising career as a Marine, instead. Embedded's new two-part series "A Good Guy" drops Thursday, October 24. To listen to this series sponsor-free and support NPR, sign up for Embedded+ in Apple Podcasts or at plus.npr.org.
title: Introducing "A Good Guy" from NPR

description: Tropical Storm Oscar brought heavy rains and winds to Cuba, an island already beleaguered by a massive power outage, late Sunday after brushing the Bahamas.
title: Oscar brings winds, heavy rains to eastern Cuba after striking the Bahamas

description: Two games in the series went to overtime.
title: The New York Liberty defeat the Minnesota Lynx to win its first WNBA championship
